WEBVTT

01:02.521 --> 01:04.857
♪ ♪

01:25.461 --> 01:27.463
♪ ♪

01:57.493 --> 01:59.495
♪ ♪

02:34.530 --> 02:36.574
Jesus, y'all, some awful news

02:36.615 --> 02:38.409
coming in from Huntsville.

02:38.450 --> 02:41.662
Multiple homicides reported
at a party on Maple.

02:41.704 --> 02:43.873
Police are on the scene...

02:48.502 --> 02:51.297
Are we safe?

02:51.338 --> 02:53.883
For now.

02:53.924 --> 02:57.303
Who is it? Who is after me?

02:57.344 --> 03:01.515
A group of Jews from New York.

03:01.557 --> 03:03.642
Well funded.

03:03.684 --> 03:08.230
Well armed. Led by a rich rat
and hungry for blood.

03:09.773 --> 03:12.735
But how do they even know
who I am?

03:12.776 --> 03:14.153
I have papers.

03:14.194 --> 03:15.404
I'm an American now.

03:15.446 --> 03:17.114
Doesn't matter.

03:17.156 --> 03:21.660
The Jews have their fiendish
ways and they're hunting us all.

03:22.953 --> 03:25.122
We must be strong.

03:26.665 --> 03:29.877
We must survive at all costs.

03:33.672 --> 03:36.133
I promise...

03:36.175 --> 03:37.676
I'll do my chores.

03:37.718 --> 03:40.179
I'll be a good girl.

03:40.220 --> 03:43.724
But let me stay, Papa. Please!

03:45.309 --> 03:47.478
My sweet girl...

03:47.519 --> 03:50.022
you're going to go
on a great adventure.

03:58.072 --> 04:00.115
We need to go.

04:01.909 --> 04:03.243
It's time.

04:03.285 --> 04:05.913
You have to go.

04:08.248 --> 04:10.000
Hear, O Israel...

04:12.461 --> 04:14.838
Home is with you always,
Rebekah.

04:16.590 --> 04:18.550
Everything's going to be fine.

04:18.592 --> 04:21.845
But you must be strong,
you understand me?

04:21.887 --> 04:23.138
You must survive...

04:23.180 --> 04:24.223
at all costs.

04:40.155 --> 04:42.157
♪ ♪

04:59.466 --> 05:01.427
Only chips?

05:01.468 --> 05:04.263
You know what?
The next time our leader's car

05:04.304 --> 05:07.307
is blown to smithereens
and our regular headquarters

05:07.349 --> 05:12.146
is compromised, I'll be sure
and prepare a brisket. Shmeckel.

05:12.187 --> 05:13.581
I didn't know
we were having company.

05:13.605 --> 05:15.566
Harriet did this.

05:15.607 --> 05:18.402
- She fucking set us up.
- Wait, wait, wait.

05:18.444 --> 05:20.612
Have we heard anything from her?

05:20.654 --> 05:23.449
Why would we hear
from a fucking traitor?

05:23.490 --> 05:25.451
Did you talk to Roxy?

05:25.492 --> 05:27.244
I've been trying her
all morning.

05:27.286 --> 05:29.079
Nothing.

05:29.121 --> 05:31.165
Last thing she said
before she jetted last night

05:31.206 --> 05:32.583
was that she was out.

05:32.624 --> 05:34.251
Looks like she meant it.

05:34.293 --> 05:35.753
Out?

05:35.794 --> 05:37.921
They found Meyer.

05:37.963 --> 05:40.340
Who knows what else
Harriet told them.

05:40.382 --> 05:42.277
- We should postpone the wedding.
- Ah... No, no, no, no.

05:42.301 --> 05:43.695
If anything were
to happen to Amy...

05:43.719 --> 05:46.055
- Nobody is postponing anything.
- Murray.

05:46.096 --> 05:48.599
They are not taking this away.
Not again.

05:50.017 --> 05:52.102
They get nothing from me.
You understand?

05:55.189 --> 05:57.649
Listen, Meyer assured me

05:57.691 --> 05:59.651
that everything's
going to be all right.

05:59.693 --> 06:01.945
He arranged for extra security.

06:01.987 --> 06:04.132
- The Kosher Nostra will be
there, so it's not
- Whoa, oh, wait.

06:04.156 --> 06:06.342
-going to be a problem.
-The fucking Jew mafia?
-Gangsters?

06:06.366 --> 06:08.786
You-you know, Bernie Flagelstein
went to them for help once.

06:08.827 --> 06:11.663
- Y-Yeah.
- Everyone knows
what happened to him.

06:11.705 --> 06:13.373
Yeah, he came back
without his flagel.

06:13.415 --> 06:16.126
Yeah. But Meyer
is not Bernie Flagelstein.

06:17.377 --> 06:20.589
The wedding will go on.

06:20.631 --> 06:22.549
- Ah, geez...
- You'll be all right.

06:22.591 --> 06:24.593
Hmm.

06:24.635 --> 06:27.429
Yeah, you're a regular
Florence Nightingale.

06:27.471 --> 06:29.264
Yeah, and you're
a regular shvantz.

06:29.306 --> 06:31.308
Ow.

06:34.353 --> 06:37.231
So you really think
Joe's gonna find The Ghost

06:37.272 --> 06:39.108
down in-in Maryland?

06:39.149 --> 06:41.693
We will hope for miracles,

06:41.735 --> 06:43.654
but we will not rely on them.

06:43.695 --> 06:45.656
Whoa.

06:45.697 --> 06:47.407
Thought this was the shitter.

06:47.449 --> 06:49.326
Groundhog's looking
for its shadow.

06:49.368 --> 06:50.828
What is that in your hand?

06:50.869 --> 06:53.247
Uh, a little
light bathroom reading.

06:53.288 --> 06:55.457
- Uh-huh?
- Found it at Tilda's.

06:55.499 --> 06:57.835
Saw the same one
at Holstedder's.

06:57.876 --> 06:59.670
Unless they're in the same
freaky book club,

06:59.711 --> 07:00.879
maybe it's something.

07:00.921 --> 07:03.173
- Find out what it means.
- Yep.

07:03.215 --> 07:05.801
Just after I drop some chocolate
dreidels into the Dead Sea.

07:05.843 --> 07:09.012
Uh, and Lonny.
About Tilda.

07:09.054 --> 07:11.014
Was I rash?
Yes.

07:11.056 --> 07:13.142
But was I wrong?

07:13.183 --> 07:14.560
Of course not.

07:14.601 --> 07:18.397
Instinct is important, Lonny.

07:18.438 --> 07:21.233
Instinct is everything.

07:21.275 --> 07:23.861
Instinct, huh?

07:23.902 --> 07:26.613
That's what made you
murder her in cold blood?

07:27.865 --> 07:30.450
In cold blood?

07:30.492 --> 07:32.119
We're in a war, Lonny.

07:35.747 --> 07:38.584
I'll take Jonah with me.
The kid's good at puzzles.

07:38.625 --> 07:41.003
No, no, no.
He's gonna stay for the wedding.

07:41.044 --> 07:44.298
Jonah's reciting
the Birkat Kohanim.

07:44.339 --> 07:45.883
Break a leg.

07:45.924 --> 07:48.069
W-Wait, wait, what? What?
W-What are you talking about?

07:48.093 --> 07:50.095
The world's going to hell
and you want me to stay

07:50.137 --> 07:51.656
- t-to say a fucking prayer? No.
- No, it-it...

07:51.680 --> 07:53.320
- No, that's not...
- The Hunt is not only

07:53.348 --> 07:56.852
- That's fucking crazy. No. No.
- About death, Jonah. No.

07:56.894 --> 07:58.896
It's about life, too.

08:00.731 --> 08:03.358
It is a great tragedy to me

08:03.400 --> 08:06.737
not to celebrate
what it is we do have.

08:06.778 --> 08:09.031
Some Nazis blew up your car.

08:09.072 --> 08:11.116
All right?
Roxy almost died, uh,

08:11.158 --> 08:13.202
Harriet turned on us
and you think that some ritual

08:13.243 --> 08:14.429
is more important
than me unraveling...

08:14.453 --> 08:17.414
I don't think it, I know it.

08:17.456 --> 08:20.459
Jonah, for centuries

08:20.500 --> 08:24.421
we've been persecuted
because of these rituals.

08:24.463 --> 08:27.299
These are the very things
that define us.

08:27.341 --> 08:28.926
That make us us.

08:28.967 --> 08:30.510
Retreating from that...

08:30.552 --> 08:32.554
That's defeat.

08:34.181 --> 08:36.808
And I'm not ready
to admit defeat.

08:36.850 --> 08:38.852
Are you?

08:48.779 --> 08:52.366
Didn't get a chance
to say goodbye the other night.

08:52.407 --> 08:55.953
Holy shit.
What happened?

08:55.994 --> 08:58.163
You were right.

08:58.205 --> 09:00.999
Two guys ambushed me
in the bathroom of that place.

09:01.041 --> 09:03.377
Jesus.

09:03.418 --> 09:05.379
I was all pissed.

09:05.420 --> 09:08.298
Figured you'd skipped out,
left me with the check.

09:08.340 --> 09:10.425
31 bucks.

09:10.467 --> 09:13.887
It just took me an hour
to get back up.

09:13.929 --> 09:17.391
I am telling you, they were FBI.

09:17.432 --> 09:19.810
Danny, we don't know that.

09:22.437 --> 09:25.232
Look, I need you to connect me
to your source again.

09:25.274 --> 09:27.234
What source?

09:27.276 --> 09:29.611
Thought I was just some kook
looking for company.

09:29.653 --> 09:31.947
Look, I'm sorry
about that, okay?

09:31.989 --> 09:34.366
I got this
black-and-blue makeover

09:34.408 --> 09:36.410
and this bruised rib
that hurts like hell

09:36.451 --> 09:38.787
every time I try to breathe,
if it makes you feel better.

09:38.829 --> 09:40.831
It doesn't make me feel better.

09:44.876 --> 09:48.255
There is a warehouse off of
Canal Street down by the water.

09:48.297 --> 09:51.133
Give me a few hours,
I'll make sure he's there.

09:51.174 --> 09:53.844
If the FBI didn't already
scare him off.

09:53.885 --> 09:56.305
But I am sitting this one out.

09:57.389 --> 09:59.057
Hope you can understand why.

10:07.024 --> 10:09.234
We're closed.

10:09.276 --> 10:10.902
Also, fuck you.

10:12.154 --> 10:14.281
Yeah, I missed you too, dude.

10:14.323 --> 10:16.325
What the hell are you
even doing here?

10:17.826 --> 10:19.661
Came to pick up my suit.

10:19.703 --> 10:22.664
And I wanted to talk to you.

10:22.706 --> 10:24.291
Obviously, not in that order.

10:24.333 --> 10:26.335
Pretty sure that suit
got thrown out,

10:26.376 --> 10:28.479
after, you know, you blew off
your best friend's funeral.

10:28.503 --> 10:30.672
Dickhead.

10:30.714 --> 10:33.216
Look, man, I brought
a peace offering, all right?

10:34.509 --> 10:36.720
Pretty meager peace offering.

10:38.347 --> 10:41.558
It's the best I can do
under the circumstances.

10:51.693 --> 10:55.614
Well, can't wait to hear these
motherfucking circumstances.

10:57.699 --> 11:00.077
Nazi Hunters?
You're fucking with me.

11:00.118 --> 11:02.537
I'm not fucking with you.

11:04.623 --> 11:08.418
Fuck. Fuck.

11:10.045 --> 11:12.005
So that guy came
into the comic book shop

11:12.047 --> 11:14.508
- looking for...
- Me.

11:14.549 --> 11:17.803
He was looking for me.
Booty's dead because of me.

11:17.844 --> 11:20.138
Jesus.

11:20.180 --> 11:24.142
Fucking Nazis, man?

11:24.184 --> 11:26.812
How was it? The funeral?

11:28.063 --> 11:29.940
Well, you know,
there were no strippers

11:29.981 --> 11:31.942
dancing on his coffin
to Led Zep, man.

11:31.983 --> 11:34.444
Whole thing was
fucking depressing.

11:34.486 --> 11:36.446
I sent fucking flowers.

11:36.488 --> 11:38.615
Yeah.

11:38.657 --> 11:40.617
Saw those.

11:40.659 --> 11:42.869
Spent all your drug money
on that display, huh?

11:42.911 --> 11:44.579
Everything my safta left me.

11:44.621 --> 11:46.623
Yeah.

11:47.999 --> 11:49.418
Were they nice?

11:51.503 --> 11:53.713
Yeah, man. They were,
they were real nice.

11:59.678 --> 12:02.180
Carol and I knew you were
in trouble with the FBI, man.

12:02.222 --> 12:04.349
- We could've helped.
- Dude, I c...

12:04.391 --> 12:09.688
I can't risk anything happening
to either one of you.

12:09.729 --> 12:11.356
That's why I've stayed away.

12:11.398 --> 12:13.191
Well, you won't have
to worry about me.

12:13.233 --> 12:15.652
I'm off to Oneonta SUNY
for orientation.

12:15.694 --> 12:17.446
It's supposed to be
all beer and boobs.

12:17.487 --> 12:20.240
- Boob-eonta.
- Boob-me-want-a.

12:20.282 --> 12:22.617
Yeah.

12:22.659 --> 12:26.246
So you just make sure
you see me before I go, okay?

12:26.288 --> 12:28.999
Come on, man.
I fucking love you, man.

12:32.085 --> 12:34.963
Couple weeks ago,
you're scared to talk to girls.

12:35.005 --> 12:39.634
Now you're hunting
fucking Nazis. Shit.

12:41.136 --> 12:43.096
You gonna be okay?

12:43.138 --> 12:45.557
Of course. Yeah.

12:48.560 --> 12:50.395
I don't know.

12:50.437 --> 12:52.063
I'll see you, man.

13:03.074 --> 13:05.035
Hola, Juanita.

13:05.076 --> 13:07.263
Did you happen to have a chance
to talk to the president about

13:07.287 --> 13:09.998
letting those South American
goods back in the U.S.?

13:10.040 --> 13:12.459
- No, Biff, I certainly didn't.
- Well, why not?

13:12.501 --> 13:14.628
Because I don't agree
with the policy.

13:14.669 --> 13:16.671
- That's why not.
- Eh, you...
Good morning.

13:16.713 --> 13:19.049
Good morning, Mr. President.

13:19.090 --> 13:20.884
Before we get started...

13:20.926 --> 13:24.971
And I think I speak
for everyone here...

13:25.013 --> 13:28.099
It surely is swell
to have you back, Biff.

13:28.141 --> 13:30.936
Thank you, Mr. President.

13:30.977 --> 13:36.566
No words can describe how much
it means to me, but I'll try.

13:36.608 --> 13:40.195
When you experience
a life-changing tragedy

13:40.237 --> 13:42.656
like the whopper thrown my way,

13:42.697 --> 13:47.035
well, you do some reevaluating
about what's important.

13:47.077 --> 13:48.995
About who you are.

13:49.037 --> 13:52.165
And you know who we are, sir?

13:52.207 --> 13:53.792
We're peanut farmers.

13:53.833 --> 13:57.462
Which is to say we're Americans.

13:57.504 --> 14:02.467
We overlook our homegrown values
at our peril.

14:02.509 --> 14:05.220
And that is why I say
Secretary Kreps' support

14:05.262 --> 14:08.473
to veto the bill
is well-intentioned but naive.

14:08.515 --> 14:11.476
I mean, does her heart
even thump

14:11.518 --> 14:14.729
- with red, white and blue blood?
- Mr. President,
that is not what...

14:14.771 --> 14:17.524
After what happened to me,
I don't know how to be governed

14:17.566 --> 14:19.901
by anything but this ticker
right here.

14:19.943 --> 14:23.154
And you know what my heart
tells me, sir?

14:23.196 --> 14:25.740
If the South Americans
can't bring their goods

14:25.782 --> 14:29.077
to market here, they're gonna
climb in bed with the Commies.

14:29.119 --> 14:31.288
Is that what we want
in our backyard?

14:31.329 --> 14:34.666
No, the only thing that we
should have in our backyards

14:34.708 --> 14:36.293
are Slip 'N Slides

14:36.334 --> 14:40.839
and wieners on the grill
and-and capitalist women

14:40.880 --> 14:45.635
in itsy-bitsy, teeny-weeny,
yellow polka-dot bikinis.

14:47.304 --> 14:51.808
So, Mr. President,
you must sign the bill

14:51.850 --> 14:53.810
to lift
the South American embargo.

14:53.852 --> 14:56.479
You lying son of a bitch!

14:59.566 --> 15:02.235
I told Juanita
this could be a problem.

15:02.277 --> 15:04.654
But you didn't listen.

15:04.696 --> 15:07.365
Just thought I needed
to be honest, sir.

15:07.407 --> 15:10.410
With Lottie and the kiddos up

15:10.452 --> 15:13.663
in that big amusement park
in the sky,

15:13.705 --> 15:16.833
I just can't keep quiet

15:16.875 --> 15:18.877
about the things that matter.

15:18.918 --> 15:21.212
Life is too short.

15:23.214 --> 15:26.468
It's just too
gosh-darn short, sir.

15:26.509 --> 15:28.720
♪ ♪

15:34.934 --> 15:38.688
I was just told to find Kenneth
Swiggens and get him out safely.

15:38.730 --> 15:40.023
By whom?

15:40.065 --> 15:42.609
I'm not at liberty to say.

15:42.651 --> 15:43.818
Who would even know...

15:43.860 --> 15:45.445
What I can say

15:45.487 --> 15:47.405
is that there is a plan.

15:47.447 --> 15:49.449
Yes?

15:50.825 --> 15:53.161
I thought you knew that.

15:53.203 --> 15:56.373
I only heard rumors.

15:56.414 --> 15:59.542
So, you never listened
to the broadcast?

15:59.584 --> 16:01.670
I don't know what that is.

16:04.130 --> 16:06.216
Uh, but I can assure you

16:06.257 --> 16:09.844
that I'm still completely
faithful to the cause.

16:09.886 --> 16:13.056
I should hope so, Herr Swiggens.

16:13.098 --> 16:16.142
Please, call me
by my German name...

16:16.184 --> 16:18.728
Moritz.

16:18.770 --> 16:20.772
And-and you are?

16:29.614 --> 16:31.616
♪ ♪

16:59.853 --> 17:01.813
Bless us, O Lord...

17:01.855 --> 17:04.357
and these, Thy gifts,

17:04.399 --> 17:07.277
which we are about to receive

17:07.318 --> 17:09.571
from Thy bounty,

17:09.612 --> 17:12.949
through Christ, our Lord.

17:12.991 --> 17:14.868
Amen.

17:14.909 --> 17:17.454
Very good.

17:17.495 --> 17:18.997
Now...

17:19.038 --> 17:21.958
let's practice before dinner.

17:23.168 --> 17:25.420
Show us, O Lord, Thy mercy.

17:27.422 --> 17:29.299
Mary, Sister.

17:29.340 --> 17:31.176
Grant us Thy salvation.

17:31.217 --> 17:34.012
Patricia, Sister.

17:34.053 --> 17:37.098
Grant us Thy salvation.

17:37.140 --> 17:39.559
And you, my dear?

17:39.601 --> 17:42.228
Rebekah.

17:44.439 --> 17:48.568
Come, tell me
your baptismal name.

17:50.570 --> 17:52.405
My name is

17:52.447 --> 17:54.699
Rebekah Kreutzer.

17:57.076 --> 17:58.620
Children.

17:58.661 --> 18:02.373
Your families have
sacrificed everything

18:02.415 --> 18:05.919
to bring you to safety.

18:05.960 --> 18:08.838
That is why you must always

18:08.880 --> 18:11.883
use your Christian name,

18:11.925 --> 18:14.844
and must forget your past.

18:17.096 --> 18:19.182
This is your...

18:19.224 --> 18:21.559
last chance to survive.

18:23.561 --> 18:27.148
There is no supper for a girl
who does not know her name.

18:35.657 --> 18:37.784
Eric, your friend is here.

18:48.419 --> 18:50.421
Hey, Eric.

18:52.632 --> 18:54.592
It's Joe.

18:54.634 --> 18:56.135
Mizushima.

18:56.177 --> 18:59.389
We did basic together...
West Hill.

18:59.430 --> 19:01.850
Remember?

19:04.644 --> 19:06.646
Well, it's beautiful here.

19:08.731 --> 19:11.150
Lots of nice things to draw.

19:14.404 --> 19:18.074
We all thought you won
the lottery when the Army

19:18.116 --> 19:20.159
sent you to Edgewood
instead of 'Nam.

19:24.038 --> 19:26.916
But now I see we were
both deployed to war.

19:29.002 --> 19:31.504
Listen, um,

19:31.546 --> 19:33.131
I'm trying to find
the motherfucker

19:33.172 --> 19:35.216
who was in charge
of these experiments.

19:35.258 --> 19:38.469
The man who did this to you.

19:38.511 --> 19:40.305
But everything is classified.

19:40.346 --> 19:43.975
No files, no witnesses.

19:44.017 --> 19:47.312
I...

19:47.353 --> 19:50.023
I need the name
of the director of medicine

19:50.064 --> 19:51.190
at Edgewood.

19:51.232 --> 19:52.775
He'd have been an older man.

19:52.817 --> 19:54.068
60s.

19:54.110 --> 19:55.361
German accent.

19:59.115 --> 20:02.160
Can you give me his name, Eric?

20:05.330 --> 20:07.749
It's okay, hey.

20:09.542 --> 20:11.961
It was good to see you.

20:21.846 --> 20:24.891
I remember you like
kung fu movies.

20:24.933 --> 20:28.811
And Westerns.

20:28.853 --> 20:31.397
I remember you used to get
on the mess hall table,

20:31.439 --> 20:33.483
and act out
your favorite scenes.

20:35.526 --> 20:38.071
I remember you had a wife

20:38.112 --> 20:40.239
and a kid.

20:44.827 --> 20:47.789
I remember you liked the Dodgers

20:47.830 --> 20:50.166
and the Isley Brothers
and, uh...

20:50.208 --> 20:51.918
What was it, uh...?

20:51.960 --> 20:53.044
Devil Dogs.

20:54.796 --> 20:57.465
I remember you were kind to me.

20:57.507 --> 21:00.969
The only one.

21:01.010 --> 21:02.971
And I remember that

21:03.012 --> 21:06.349
you made me feel like I was...

21:06.391 --> 21:09.185
a person.

21:10.853 --> 21:12.689
A person.

21:37.839 --> 21:39.465
Thank you.

21:43.469 --> 21:45.471
Thank you.

21:49.517 --> 21:51.477
A mystery unfolded in
Westchester, New York,

21:51.519 --> 21:54.605
as a car explosion claimed the
